<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFGifford.2C_James">Gifford, James (Year Unknown) (PDF). <i><a href="http://www.nitrosyncretic.com/rah/ftp/fedrlsvc.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.nitrosyncretic.com/rah/ftp/fedrlsvc.pdf" rel="nofollow">The Nature of Federal Service in Starship Troopers</a></i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.nitrosyncretic.com/rah/ftp/fedrlsvc.pdf" class="external free" title="http://www.nitrosyncretic.com/rah/ftp/fedrlsvc.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.nitrosyncretic.com/rah/ftp/fedrlsvc.pdf</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Nature+of+Federal+Service+in+Starship+Troopers&amp;rft.aulast=Gifford%2C+James&amp;rft.au=Gifford%2C+James&amp;rft.date=Year+Unknown&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nitrosyncretic.com%2Frah%2Fftp%2Ffedrlsvc.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Starship_Troopers"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFHeinlein2003"><a href="/wiki/Robert_A._Heinlein" title="Robert A. Heinlein">Heinlein, Robert A.</a> (2003). <i><a href="/wiki/Expanded_Universe_(Heinlein)" title="Expanded Universe (Heinlein)">Expanded Universe</a></i>. Baen. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0743471598" class="internal">ISBN 0-7434-7159-8</a>. <a href="/wiki/Online_Computer_Library_Center" title="Online Computer Library Center">OCLC</a> <a href="http://worldcat.org/oclc/223822885" class="external text" title="http://worldcat.org/oclc/223822885" rel="nofollow">223822885</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%5B%5BExpanded+Universe+%28Heinlein%29%7CExpanded+Universe%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=Heinlein&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert+A.&amp;rft.au=Heinlein%2C+Robert+A.&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.pub=Baen&amp;rft_id=info:oclcnum/223822885&amp;rft.isbn=0-7434-7159-8&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Starship_Troopers"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Contains Heinlein's comments on the writing and the politics of <i>Starship Troopers</i>, as well as the polemical speech "The Pragmatics of Patriotism" on the moral basis of the military.</li>
</ul>
